<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Matthew 1:1-25</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="28">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="25">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">The book of the history of Jesus Christ, son of David, son of Abraham:</span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Abraham became father to Isaac;<br><span class="p">Isaac became father to Jacob;</span><br><span class="p">Jacob became father to Judah and his brothers;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Judah became father to Pe&acute;rez and to Ze&acute;rah by Ta&acute;mar;<br><span class="p">Pe&acute;rez became father to Hez&acute;ron;</span><br><span class="p">Hez&acute;ron became father to Ram;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Ram became father to Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab;<br><span class="p">Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab became father to Nah&acute;shon;</span><br><span class="p">Nah&acute;shon became father to Sal&acute;mon;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Sal&acute;mon became father to Bo&acute;az by Ra&acute;hab;<br><span class="p">Bo&acute;az became father to O&acute;bed by Ruth;</span><br><span class="p">O&acute;bed became father to Jes&acute;se;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Jes&acute;se became father to David the king.<br><span class="p">&nbsp;David became father to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon by the wife of U&middot;ri&acute;ah;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Sol&acute;o&middot;mon became father to Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am;<br><span class="p">Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am became father to A&middot;bi&acute;jah;</span><br><span class="p">A&middot;bi&acute;jah became father to A&acute;sa;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">A&acute;sa became father to Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat;<br><span class="p">Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat became father to Je&middot;ho&acute;ram;</span><br><span class="p">Je&middot;ho&acute;ram became father to Uz&middot;zi&acute;ah;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Uz&middot;zi&acute;ah became father to Jo&acute;tham;<br><span class="p">Jo&acute;tham became father to A&acute;haz;</span><br><span class="p">A&acute;haz became father to Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah became father to Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh;<br><span class="p">Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh became father to A&acute;mon;</span><br><span class="p">A&acute;mon became father to Jo&middot;si&acute;ah;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Jo&middot;si&acute;ah became father to Jec&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;ah and to his brothers at the time of the deportation to Babylon.</span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">After the deportation to Babylon Jec&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;ah became father to She&middot;al&acute;ti&middot;el;<br><span class="p">She&middot;al&acute;ti&middot;el became father to Ze&middot;rub&acute;ba&middot;bel;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Ze&middot;rub&acute;ba&middot;bel became father to A&middot;bi&acute;ud;<br><span class="p">A&middot;bi&acute;ud became father to E&middot;li&acute;a&middot;kim;</span><br><span class="p">E&middot;li&acute;a&middot;kim became father to A&acute;zor;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">A&acute;zor became father to Za&acute;dok;<br><span class="p">Za&acute;dok became father to A&acute;chim;</span><br><span class="p">A&acute;chim became father to E&middot;li&acute;ud;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">E&middot;li&acute;ud became father to El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar;<br><span class="p">El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar became father to Mat&acute;than;</span><br><span class="p">Mat&acute;than became father to Jacob;</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Jacob became father to Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom Jesus was born, who is called Christ.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">All the generations, then, from Abraham until David were fourteen generations, and from David until the deportation to Babylon fourteen generations, and from the deportation to Babylon until the Christ fourteen generations.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">But the birth of Jesus Christ was in this way. During the time his mother Mary was promised in marriage to Joseph, she was found to be pregnant by holy spirit before they were united.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">However, Joseph her husband, because he was righteous and did not want to make her a public spectacle, intended to divorce her secretly.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">But after he had thought these things over, look! Jehovah’s angel appeared to him in a dream, saying: “Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary your wife home, for that which has been begotten in her is by holy spirit.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">She will give birth to a son, and you must call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.”</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">All this actually came about for that to be fulfilled which was spoken by Jehovah through his prophet, saying:</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">“Look! The virgin will become pregnant and will give birth to a son, and they will call his name Im&middot;man&acute;u&middot;el,” which means, when translated, “With Us Is God.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Then Joseph woke up from his sleep and did as the angel of Jehovah had directed him, and he took his wife home.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">But he had no intercourse with her until she gave birth to a son; and he called his name Jesus.</span>
</p>
</form>

